column5: Headed out with Cal and troutguy today for a quick fish.  We were out for about 4 hours, moving from 90-99 feet of water.  We marked lots of fish, but nothing overly aggressive.  Cal landed a nice whitie, I got 2 whities and Ryan landed 3 lakers.  Not a bad outing, all fish today were caught on tubes.        Thanks for reading,  Steve Rowbotham Owner/Operator, Sir Catch-A-Lot Pro Guiding
Nice fish  Good for getting out and thanks for the report!
Nice goin'! What was the ice like?   ... and do you need someone to help drill some holes the next time you're out?
Great report and pics Steve  Looks like you guys had a great couple hours out there... nice whities Thanks for sharing Leechman

Ive never caught a whitie first hand , never even saw one in person, only time ive seen one is on this board lol, Sorry, there just not on the list of available species in the water i fish    But im curious why there mouths always seem to be  so red. Are they easy bleeders, is it just the color of their mouth, whats the scoop.
mmmm VERY NOICE!  thank you for making us eat mud.  HD

Blaque - whitefish like to wear bright red lipstick, just in case the fisherman whe gets them gives them a smooch. They are very sexy fish LOL. Seriously though - I don't know why they have such red mouths... maybe related to them bleeding from the gills sometimes since they are often caught and brought up from really deep water.  p.s. Steve - I am still troutless LOL!!! But see my whiteys report from Monday, had a great day!
thanks guys, who's all fishing closing weekend ?
March 31st is the last day in QC and will be fishing if the weather holds and ice is still good
Do you start wearing water wings near the end?    I'm hoping to get out once more on Saturday or Sunday.
No.... last year we were able to fish until the 31st and it was a hot and beautiful day.  Managed to get a sun burn  lol
